Shell Script

üëâ A shell script is a file containing multiple Linux commands executed automatically.

Example:

#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello Linux"

1-Line Interview Answer

Shell is a command-line interface that allows users to communicate with the Linux kernel by executing commands.

